---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const schema = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "General Handyman Services Phillip Island",
      "provider": {
        "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
        "name": "Mr Home Assist",
        "image": "https://mrhomeassist.com.au/images/handyman.webp"
      },
      "areaServed": ["Cowes", "San Remo", "Bass Coast"],
      "description": "Professional handyman services for Phillip Island. Furniture assembly, door repairs, plaster patching, and lock replacement."
    }
  ]
});
---

<Layout title="Handyman Phillip Island | Small Jobs & Property Repairs" description="The local fix-it expert for Cowes and San Remo. Doors, locks, plaster, flyscreens, and furniture assembly. No job too small. Call 56 789 012." schema={schema}>
    
    <section class="relative bg-slate-900 py-32 lg:py-48 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 z-0">
            <img src="/images/handyman.webp" alt="Professional handyman toolbelt and ladder in a hallway" class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-30" />
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-slate-900 via-slate-900/50 to-transparent"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
            <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold text-white mb-6">
                Your Local <span class="text-orange-500">Fix-It</span> Expert
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
                Sticking doors? Hole in the wall? Flat-pack furniture still in the box? We handle the "Too Hard Basket" for homeowners and real estate agents across the Bass Coast.
            </p>
            <a href="#contact" class="inline-block bg-orange-600 text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-xl hover:bg-orange-500 transition-colors">
                Get a Quick Quote
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-24 bg-white px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">No Job Too Small</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-600 mb-16">
                <p>
                    Finding a trade for small jobs on Phillip Island can be impossible. Builders want whole houses; plumbers want renovations. <strong>Mr Home Assist</strong> fills that gap. We specialize in the small, annoying repairs that keep your home functioning.
                </p>
                
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-12 not-prose">
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-3">Door & Window Repairs</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm">Salt air swells timber frames, making doors stick. We plane doors, replace rusted hinges with stainless steel, and re-mesh flyscreens that have been torn by pets or coastal winds.</p>
                    </div>
                     <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-3">Plaster & Painting</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm">From door handle holes to settling cracks. We professionally patch, sand, and paint-match so you can't see the repair. Perfect for rental bond recovery.</p>
                    </div>
                     <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-3">Locks & Security</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm">Corroded locks are a common issue in Cowes. We supply and install new deadlocks, window winders, and screen door closers to keep your property secure.</p>
                    </div>
                     <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg mb-3">General Installation</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm">Hanging pictures, mirrors, dryers, tv brackets, and towel rails. We have the correct fixings for plasterboard, brick, and masonry walls.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

             <!-- The Handbook -->
            <div class="bg-sky-50 border border-sky-100 rounded-3xl p-10">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
                    <span class="bg-sky-100 text-sky-700 p-2 rounded-lg">
                         <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"/></svg>
                    </span>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 m-0">The Maintenance Handbook</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-sm">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-sky-900 mb-2">Smoke Alarm Legislation (VIC)</h4>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                            All rental properties in Victoria must have smoke alarms tested annually. We can inspect, battery-change, and replace expired units (older than 10 years) to keep you compliant with tenancy laws.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-sky-900 mb-2">Coastal Corrosion Protection</h4>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
                            For outdoor fittings (gate latches, hose reels), we recommend applying a lanolin-based spray (Lanotec) every 6 months. This creates a natural barrier against the salty Bass Coast air.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>

</Layout>
